For {= site_name_location_region =}+ named physical EV charging host sites, identify each site by site name, location, and region; for each site, cover each of the {= provenance_role =} provenance roles listed below with a site-specific source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL under each role).

The evidence is public provenance about specific sites that host, are listed for, or are publicly proposed, awarded, approved, funded, permitted, or planned for EV charging. Together, the provenance roles require source-diverse project proof rather than one bulk public table, locator page, or chain location page. A broad program page can support the public-program role when it has a site-specific row, but it does not also become site-dedicated or independent proof for that site. It is not a host ranking, procurement recommendation, outreach list, contact search, lead score, installation recommendation, supplier comparison, or legal, engineering, safety, or compliance conclusion.

Provenance roles:
- `program_award_trace`: a public agency, public utility, grant, incentive, RFP, award, selected-site, contract, or make-ready program record that binds the physical site to EV charging project provenance.
- `local_permit_planning_trace`: a local permit, planning, zoning, site-plan, public-notice, agenda, staff-report, hearing, inspection, or comparable local approval/process surface for the site's EV charging project.
- `site_dedicated_project_surface`: a host, property, parking, public-facility, utility, or operator-controlled page, section, notice, or announcement whose subject is the individual named site/project, not merely a generic store/location page, station-status page, citywide program page, all-sites table, or bulk project list.
- `independent_local_trace`: an independent local, trade, property, parking-authority, community, or institutional source that separately describes the same site's EV charging project context without being the bulk program table, host/location page, or station-status page already used for another role.

Sites ought to be specific physical facilities or project locations, not charging networks, charging vendors, broad chains without a specific location, citywide or corridor-wide programs, generic eligibility pages, or broad public-property categories. Different addresses under the same chain count as distinct sites; alternate names for the same property, garage, mall, station, or project location count as the same site. Broad tables, appendices, PDFs, and program pages can count only for the role whose source context they actually fit, and only when the cited row, section, or passage visibly binds the named site/location to a site-specific EV charging project trace. Pure charging-operator station pages, locator details, live status pages, generic chain store pages, all-stations inventories, and citywide location-list pages are not root public/project provenance by themselves unless the same page also carries the role-specific public project, permit/planning, site-dedicated project, or independent local provenance required for the declared role.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the named physical site or a site/project at the same location. A generic chain page, citywide program page, public-incentive page, or network landing page is not enough unless it names, addresses, table-entry-binds, or otherwise visibly singles out the specific named site/location.
- The page should make its provenance-role source fit visible: for `program_award_trace`, it should read as a public agency, public utility, grant/incentive, RFP, award, selected-site, contract, public make-ready, DOT/energy-office, or comparable program source for the named site; for `local_permit_planning_trace`, it should read as a local permit, planning, zoning, site-plan, public-notice, agenda, staff-report, hearing, inspection, or comparable local process source for the named site; for `site_dedicated_project_surface`, it should read as a host, property, parking, public-facility, utility, or operator-controlled page, section, notice, or announcement whose subject is the individual named site/project, not merely a generic location page, chain services page, station locator, citywide program page, all-sites table, or bulk location/project list; for `independent_local_trace`, it should read as an independent local, trade, property, parking-authority, community, or institutional source about the named site's charging project context, not the bulk program table, host/location page, station-status page, public registry detail, locator, or all-sites inventory used by the other roles.
- The page must expose a concrete role-scoped public fact about the site or charging project: for `program_award_trace`, a program/award/project fact such as selected-site status, award, application, grant amount, contract, corridor/exit, utility make-ready scope, timeline, charger count, or public-program status; for `local_permit_planning_trace`, a permit, planning, site-plan, hearing, staff-report, approval, inspection, public-comment, or local process fact; for `site_dedicated_project_surface`, a site-dedicated project/host/utility fact such as a host announcement, property project page, facility charging project page, parking/public-facility EV page, make-ready project page, single-site notice, or operator project announcement whose subject is the named site; for `independent_local_trace`, a separately sourced local or institutional fact that ties the same physical site to the EV charging project context.
